Program: Discovery
Title: Why elephants never forget
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry4y
Last Broadcast Date: 03 July 2002
A report on how elephants use their sixth 'seismic' sense. Scientists are looking at how elephants have the ability to generate seismic vibrations to communicate messages to other elephants, ground vibrations also travel further than acoustic waves.